Reasoning: The paper deals with the topology of wireless communication maps and their usability in algorithmic design, which suggests that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the algorithmic challenges of designing efficient point location techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also studies the geometry of SINR diagrams, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new variant of approximate point location, which suggests that it could belong to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
